            "
          >
            Russia quits nuclear pact
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image
          border-radius="10px"
          padding="10px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/russia-withdrawal-inf-treaty.jpg"
          alt="Historical image of Mikhail Gorbachev and Ronald Reagan smiling as they sign the INF disarmament treaty, symbolizing Cold War diplomacy, with modern concerns over Russia’s withdrawal from the pact."
          href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com"
        />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>
              US President Ronald Reagan and Soviet leader Mikhail Gorbachev
              sign the INF Treaty banning intermediate‑range nuclear missiles,
              Washington, DC, December 8, 1987. Source: Marshall Center</i
            >
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The what:</strong> Russia has officially left the 1987
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-aug-25-spotlight-h1-1-intermediate-range-nuclear-forces-inf-treaty?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >Intermediate-Range Nuclear Forces (INF) Treaty</a
            >, which banned ground-launched missiles with ranges between 500 and
            5,500 kilometres and led to the destruction of over 2,600 missiles.
            The US left the treaty in 2019 (during Trump’s first term), accusing
            Moscow of violations, but Russia had stayed nominally committed
            until this point.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The why:</strong> The Russian Foreign Ministry said it ended
            its self-imposed moratorium on these weapons because of the movement
            of US missile systems into Europe, the Philippines, and Australia,
            calling it a direct threat to Moscow’s security. Former president
            Dmitry Medvedev added that the move was a response to NATO
            countries’ anti-Russian policy, and hinted that more escalatory
            steps may come (<a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-aug-25-spotlight-h1-2-x-post?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >X post</a
            >).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The relevance:</strong> The treaty’s collapse adds to
            nuclear tensions between Russia and the West. In response to
            Medvedev’s threats, President Trump sent
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-aug-25-spotlight-h1-3-two-us-nuclear-submarines?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >two US nuclear submarines</a
            >
            to the region. While experts caution against overreacting to Russian
            rhetoric, the elimination of treaty limits increases strategic
            uncertainty and risks a Cold War–style arms race.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Thirty-one countries currently possess ballistic missiles (<a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-aug-25-spotlight-h1-4-chart?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >chart</a
            >).
          </p>
        </mj-text>
